questionListItems.title: Why I have been billed on days when I didn't drive?

answer.body:
Our app batches up multiple past parking sessions into a single card statement. Parking sessions payments will be batched every $5 or 2 days (whichever is earlier) into bills. This is to reduce clutter on your card statements.


Please do not be alarmed were billed on days you did not park your vehicle. You may find that some Bill IDs contain only one session whereas some are a combination of two or more sessions. To check your payment history, simply refer to the 'BILL' tab under the History page in the app. There, you can match the Bill IDs and their charges against the assigned Bill ID under your credit card statement.

However, if you still feel that the charges are wrong, please email feedback@parking.sg with the following details:


  1. Picture of your card statement (please exclude sensitive information)

  2. Screenshot of your parking history in the parking app (click into "HISTORY" from the top left drop-down menu)

  3. Your vehicle number

questionListItems.title: I have change my credit card. How to update my new credit card

answer.body: To change the existing credit card being used in the app now, you can simply tap on "REMOVE CARD" in the top left drop-down menu. Once you are done with that, you can tap on "ADD CARD" from the same top left drop-down menu and proceed to enter your new credit card information.

answer.body:
This is because our app batches up multiple past parking sessions into a single card statement to reduce clutter on your card statements.


Parking sessions payments will be batched every $5 or 2 days (whichever is earlier) into bills. So, you may find that some Bill IDs contain only one session whereas some are a combination of two or more sessions.

questionListItems.title: How do I pay for my parking sessions?

answer.body: Currently, you can pay for your sessions with Visa, MasterCard and American Express debit and credit cards. If this is the first time using the app, you will be prompted to enter your credit or debit card details before you start the parking session. Alternatively, you can tap to the menu button on the top left hand corner and tap on “Add Card”.

questionListItems.title: Phone changed, how to retrieve parking history?
questionListItems.body: once i changed my phone, all the parking history in the app are gone, may i know how to retrieve last month parking history?

answer.body: If you removed the parking app from your phone, your parking history will be erased. If you still have the app on your previous phone, you can export the history from there. Otherwise, email us your vehicle number and we can pull the information for you.

questionListItems.title: I renewed my credit card recently. How do I update the expiry date for Parking.SG?

answer.body:
To update your credit card details, just follow these simple steps:

  1. Tap on the "REMOVE CARD" button in the top left drop-down menu.

  2. After removing the existing card, tap on "ADD CARD" from the same menu.

  3. Enter the details of your new credit card. That's it! Your new card will now be saved in the app and ready to use for your next transactions.

questionListItems.title: What happens if I forget to end my parking session?

answer.body: If you forget to end your parking session, it will expire automatically after the initial specified parking duration. To avoid being charged extra fees, make sure to end your parking session before it expires. If you need more time, you can extend your parking session using the app or website. Simply follow the instructions on how to extend your parking session on your chosen platform.

questionListItems.title: My card has expired. How do I replace it with the new replacement & expiry date?

answer.body:
To replace your existing credit card in the app, follow these simple steps:

  1. Tap on the "REMOVE CARD" option in the top left drop-down menu.

  2. After removing the old card, tap on "ADD CARD" from the same drop-down menu.

  3. Enter the details of your new credit card as prompted.

  4. Make sure to double-check your information before submitting it.

That's it! Your new credit card should now be updated and ready to use in the app.

questionListItems.title: Parking hours ended at 10pm at Jalan Sultan but i had to select parking period which extended to 10.15pm & was charged till 10.15pm. How do i get a refund for the extra 15mins?

answer.body: Our app takes free parking into account when calculating your parking charges. For example, if a car park is $0.60 per half hour from 8:30 am to 10 pm, and free parking from 10 pm to 8:30 am, and you park at 9:30 pm for 1 hour, the app will only count your parking charges from 9:30 pm to 10 pm, and it won't charge you for the free parking period from 10 pm onwards. Therefore, you will only be charged $0.60.

questionListItems.title: I want to check what is the credit card being used. I may need to replace. Too worried to select remove card.

answer.body:
To check your credit card details, follow these simple steps:


  1. Tap on the Menu icon (three lines on the top left corner) in the app.

  2. Select "Remove Card". Rest assured, this will not remove your card details yet. Use this page to see the last 4 digit of your card number.

To replace your existing credit card in the app, continue with the following steps:


  1. Remove your card by tapping on the “REMOVE” button.

  2. After removing the old card, tap on "ADD CARD" from the same drop-down menu.

  3. Enter the details of your new credit card as prompted.

  4. Make sure to double-check your information before submitting. That's it! Your new credit card should now be updated and ready to use in the app.

questionListItems.title: Can I start a parking session on behalf of another person?

answer.body: Yes, you can start a parking session on behalf of someone else, but you need to enter their vehicle and parking details in the app to do so. Keep in mind that only one session can be activated per app at a time. Find more information on how to start a session here.

Yes, you can park your car overnight if the car park has the night parking scheme. The night parking max charge of $5 will apply automatically in the computation of parking charges. Just check if the car park has a night parking scheme before leaving your car overnight. If you're unsure, contact the parking operator or the HDB customer service hotline for more information.
